post_text: Students at Polk Street School had the opportunity to meet award-winning author Dan Gutman this week. Mr. Gutman read one of his books and even gave students a sneak peek of an upcoming book from the My Weird School series. Students asked questions and also learned about the process Mr. Gutman uses to write. Thank you to Ms. Subbiondo and the PSS PTA for organizing this fantastic event.

post_text: Last night, the Franklin Square School Board honored Mia and Kylie Hennelly with an Act of Kindness award for their part in raising over $2200 for local families as part of the #friendswhogive campaign. These Washington Street School students donated $2000 in gift cards to the administration to provide to members of our community. We are so proud of their efforts and look forward to their continued success.

post_text:
Dear Franklin Square Families:

During the last week, our community has been filled with performances, concerts, class celebrations, decorations and holiday boutiques. The spirit of the season has certainly been in the air. On behalf of my family and my district family, I would like to take this opportunity to wish you and your loved ones happy holidays and a very Happy New Year.
Enjoy the next two weeks. We look forward to welcoming everyone back to school on January 6, 2020.

Best,

Dr. Jared Bloom

post_text:
Ms. Sollenne and Ms. Romanelli's class at WSS read THANKSGIVING MICE for story time. Students enjoyed the book and had fun acting out parts of the story, especially when the Mayflower landed at Plymouth Rock.

**For many days the Pilgrim mice in stormy seas tossed to and fro. They huddled, seasick, in the hold, hungry, thirsty, filled with dread. At last their journey came to an end. The mice all shouted, "Land ahead!"**

post_text: Congratulations to Vito Scatigno, a custodian at Washington Street School, for receiving the first Franklin Square UFSD Act of Kindness Award at the November Board meeting. Mr. Scatigno went above and beyond to replace the motor on a student’s costume prior to the Halloween parade at Washington Street School. We appreciate his willingness to go above and beyond to help out. If you would like to nominate a staff member for an Act of Kindness award, please email Dr. Bloom.
